OL,7,FSeveral providers offer contracts that
OL,8,Fdo not contain price rises, while
OL,9,Fothers offer deals that allow for
OL,10,Funspecified price rises during the
OL,11,Fcontract period.
OL,13,FIf they do this, they must give
OL,14,Fcustomers 30 days' notice and the
OL,15,Fright to exit penalty-free, so
OL,16,Fconsumers can avoid the increase.
OL,18,FUswitch telecoms spokesman Ernest Doku
OL,19,Fdescribed Ofcom's new rules as a
OL,20,F"transparency tax for consumers".
